# RayBen445 Portfolio - Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env.local for local development

# Telegram Integration (Required for Contact Form)
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=your_telegram_bot_token_here
TELEGRAM_USER_ID=your_telegram_user_id_here

# Google AI Integration (Required for AI Features)
GOOGLE_API_KEY=your_google_api_key_here

# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file: cp .env.example .env.local
# 2. Replace the placeholder values with your actual keys
# 3. Never commit .env.local to git (it's already in .gitignore)
# 4. For Vercel deployment, set these same variables in your Vercel dashboard

# How to get these values:
# TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN: Message @BotFather on Telegram, create a new bot
# TELEGRAM_USER_ID: Message @userinfobot on Telegram to get your user ID
# GOOGLE_API_KEY: Create one at https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials